  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the<strong> tofu</strong> and pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the<strong> tofu</strong> into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Combine the<strong> ground cumin</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong> in a large bowl, add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu cubes</strong> to the bowl and mix until everything is evenly coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>pak choi</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the base off the <strong>pak choi</strong> and discard, then slice the rest finely</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate the <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu cubes</strong> and cook for 6-8 min, turning occasionally until crisp</p><p>Once the<strong> </strong>tofu is crisp, transfer it to kitchen paper and set aside (save the pan!) – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1865.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
